<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,295,538]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,320,295,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Classification.</emphasis>
The families 
<taxonomicName authority="Dana, 1853" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" box="[482,749,295,322]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Synopiidae 
<bibRefCitation author="Dana, J. D." box="[617,749,295,322]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="689 - 1618" refId="ref48889" refString="Dana, J. D. (1853) Crustacea. Part II. United States Exploring Expedition during the years 1838, 1830, 1840, 1841, 1842, under the command of Charles Wilkes, U. S. N., 13 (2), 689 - 1618." type="journal article" year="1853">Dana, 1853</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Stebbing, 1906" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1906" box="[808,1097,295,321]" class="Malacostraca" family="Tironidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Tironidae 
<bibRefCitation author="Stebbing, T. R. R." box="[925,1097,295,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 806" refId="ref50350" refString="Stebbing, T. R. R. (1906) Amphipoda I. Gammaridea. Das Tierreich, 21, 1 - 806." type="journal article" year="1906">Stebbing, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
were synonymized under the former name by J.L. 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnard, J. L." box="[387,562,331,358]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="3 - 46" refId="ref48341" refString="Barnard, J. L. (1964) Deep-Sea Amphipoda (Crustacea) Collected by the R / V Vema in the Eastern Pacific Ocean and the Caribbean and Mediterranean Seas. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 127, 3 - 46." type="journal article" year="1964">Barnard (1964)</bibRefCitation>
, a move that has not been disputed, and which then included the genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Lilljeborg, 1865" authorityName="Lilljeborg" authorityYear="1865" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Tiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1377,1437,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Tiron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lilljeborg, W." box="[151,336,367,394]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref49856" refString="Lilljeborg, W. (1865) On the Lysianassa magellanica H. Milne Edwards, and on the Crustacea of the suborder Amphipoda and subfamily Lysianassina found an [sic] the coast of Sweden and Norway. Nova Acta Regiae Societatis Scientiarum Upsaliensis, Series 3, 61, 1 - 38. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6806" type="journal article" year="1865">Lilljeborg, 1865</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 7 species and 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevreux, 1895" authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="1895" box="[570,898,367,394]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Pseudotiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[570,706,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Pseudotiron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chevreux, E." box="[716,898,367,394]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="165 - 170" refId="ref48758" refString="Chevreux, E. (1895) Sur un Amphipode, Pseudotiron bouvieri, nov. gen. et sp., de la Famille des Syrrhoidae nouvelle pour la Fauna Mediterranenne. Bulletin de la Societe Zoologique de France, 20, 165 - 170. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 29691" type="journal article" year="1895">Chevreux, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 2 species. These 2 genera and 9 species, together with 4 new genera and an additional 32 species described since 1964 (including 18 here), differ distinctly from the remaining synopiids. A new subfamily for this group of genera is diagnosed as 
<taxonomicName authority="Stebbing 1906" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1906" box="[1158,1432,439,465]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tironinae">
Tironinae 
<bibRefCitation author="Stebbing, T. R. R." box="[1274,1432,439,465]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 806" refId="ref50350" refString="Stebbing, T. R. R. (1906) Amphipoda I. Gammaridea. Das Tierreich, 21, 1 - 806." type="journal article" year="1906">Stebbing1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,259,475,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">stat. nov.</emphasis>
Further analysis of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" box="[532,658,475,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Synopiidae</taxonomicName>
is needed to ascertain its full subfamilial structure, which is beyond the scope of this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
